  "HEADLINE": "Of the 7 G>A-wobble drivers the RNA toehold can't sense, 5/7 ARE CRISPR-addressable by SpCas9 (NGG) allele-specific guides \u2014 1 via a PAM-CREATING SNV (mutant makes an NGG the WT lacks = gold-standard allele specificity) and the rest via a PAM-proximal SEED mismatch. NOT rescued by NGG (need NG/Cas12a or another Cas): ['TP53_R175H', 'TP53_R273H'] This CONVERTS RUNG-27b's asserted DNA-rescue into a designed, sequence-verified set of allele-specific guides \u2014 the wobble drivers (incl. KRAS-G12D, IDH1-R132H, TP53 hotspots) are reachable at the DNA level with real guides, not just by assumption.",
  "INTERPRETATION_MAP": {
    "PAM_CREATED": "mutation creates an NGG the WT lacks -> guide+PAM hits mutant ONLY (perfect allele specificity).",
    "SEED": "shared PAM, SNV in PAM-proximal 10 nt -> WT has a seed mismatch -> Cas9 activity collapses on WT.",
    "NOT rescued by NGG": "no NGG PAM-creating/seed option in CDS-local context -> try SpCas9-NG / Cas12a, or the genomic (intron-aware) context may add PAMs (the refinement)."
  },
  "CEILING": [
